<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12005j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12005j">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12005j"> 5(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cromlech petrified / dancing girls</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Et ce <mark>cromlec&apos;h</mark>, ces gros blocs qui forment un cercle si curieux sur une colline, au-dessus du joli bourg de Langon, pourquoi les nomme-t-on <mark>les Danseuses</mark>? Parce que des jeunes filles, coquettes et frivoles, se livraient, durant un bel apr&egrave;s-midi d&apos;&eacute;t&eacute;, &agrave; leur plaisir favori, et qu&apos;elles ne voulurent pas interrompre leur ronde pour s&apos;agenouiller devant une procession qui passait. Alors leurs bras, leurs jambes se raidirent et depuis ce temps, elles sont l&agrave; <mark>p&eacute;trifi&eacute;es</mark>, attendant sous l&apos;enveloppe de granit qui &eacute;treint leur corps le jugement supr&ecirc;me o&ugrave; compara&icirc;tra l&apos;humanit&eacute; enti&egrave;re. <br><font color="green">[And this cromlech, these large blocks that form such a curious circle on a hill, beneath the pretty market town of Langon, why do they call it the dancing girls? Because some young girls, coquettish and frivolous, surrendered themselves one lovely Summer afternoon to their favourite pleasure and they did not want to interrupt their <i>roundelay</i> to kneel before a procession that was passing by. Therefore their arms and legs stiffened and ever since this time they have remained petrified there, waiting under the granite envelope that embraces their bodies for the final judgement, which will befall all humanity.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 17</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
